    <h1>Am&#xAD;bi&#xAD;ence</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200906/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-06"><time>2020-09-06</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE I FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Kim Yam Road (far right) is more hip with its raw wooden ta­bles and shelves lined with sauces and snacks.</p>
    <p>But be­cause it shares space with a cafe, it is a lit­tle dis­ori­ent­ing when you’re the only ta­ble hav­ing din­ner while oth­ers are quaffing beer and shoot­ing the breeze.</p>
    <p>Also, you have to or­der at the counter, though you can opt to pay at the end of the meal.</p>
    <p>Hill­crest Road (right) is a gar­den-va­ri­ety fam­ily restau­rant that is more con­ven­tional in com­par­i­son. But its well-spaced ta­bles en­sure more pri­vacy and older folk will find din­ing there more com­fort­able.</p>

